The paper deals with the problem of identifying malicious IP addresses from unstructured text data in security forums. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses matrix decomposition and textual analysis techniques, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on automated data collection and analysis could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
